han men did.  And that was true, also, in Libya.  [Women were the] repositories of genealogical knowledge. If you and I were chatting, and your wife was over there at the back of a one-room house, doing something or other, and I would say, \'93
Well, who is he?\'94  And \'93Is he some relative of yours?\'94  And so the wife would say, \'93Yes, he\rquote s your brother\rquote s wife\rquote s cousin\'94, and so on.  So they knew all the connections.  That didn\rquote 
